The stable keeper mixes proper feed for the horses to keep them strong and healthy.
Always offer the pigs a balanced diet of mash and discarded vegetable scraps.
Daily scratching in the dirt helps the chickens find tasty insects and grit.
Roosting bars offer a perfect place for the flock to sleep securely every night.
Shearing begins with careful preparation to ensure the sheep are calm.
Wool is carefully collected and weighed immediately after the shearing process concludes.
Brushing the horse daily helps maintain its coat and encourages bonding.
Grooming includes cleaning the ears and eyes to keep the horse comfortable and clean.
